attributedString.string: Use labels for spelling out things like text color, border color, font, and so on.  Its basically just text you can use anywhere.
Use reference tags to label elements that have already been specd out in another document.  Remember, you dont need to spec something out that has already been done.  Use the tag!
Use measurement indicators when the thing youre designing has an explicit width or height, or both.  These always go on the right or bottom sides, never the top or left.
Use lines to point at things.  Duh!  Usually, you will write out specs for borders, fonts and such using the Label, and then use a line to point from the label to the thing it describes.
When detailing different style attributes, follow the syntax conventions shown to the right.

x-axis: X y-axis: X blur: X spread: X
shadow: X 1px, Y 0px, blur 4px, spread 2px
Use stack spacing to indicate the vertical space between elements
Use square inset spacing to indicate the amount of inset spacing on all sides of a container.
Use inline spacing to indicate the horizontal space betwee elements inside a component or group.
Use the dashed box indicator to show the dimensions of elements that are borderless and have no background.

Composition Images describe the general, structural parts of a component. For example a component may have a container, a header, a content area, and a footer.

Use the circle-end line for indicating composition elements.

Style specification images call out the specific attributes of a given components, often representing CSS values.

Redline specifications must be to the right of the image, with the text being left justified, as shown here.

Do not add redline specifications for elements that have already been specd in their own file.  Use the pill shaped Reference Tag to show that an element is a separate component.

Use the arrow-ended redlines for indicating style for elements.

Spacing specifications must follow the standards outlined in the Spacing System article.  These images should show inset spacing for containers, and spacing between elements within the component.

Do not show spacing outside of the component, unless it is in relation to another element inside a larger component.

Use spacing and dimensions indicators for spacing images.
